1eb7e1b02c9fb306.voiceContent: Let's activate the mechanism in front of us first, just like before. See if that changes anything

0120c0bb610df3cc.voiceContent: If you ever see any stickers on my back, do me a favor and take them off... Melusines like to play pranks sometimes

09fb9de6ac31fd18.voiceContent: I've managed to get myself to a pretty comfortable place in life, but there's still some things I want that are outside my reach, like a peaceful and happy childhood, or the ability to trust other people. Maybe some people would see those feelings as shameful or contradictory, but I don't see a problem with sharing them. After all, why should anybody be afraid to admit what they want

1299bcaa5161799a.voiceContent: Word of advice Don't break the law. Hmm, is there anything else? Oh, yeah... Seriously, don't break the law

18128a17f3f67df7.voiceContent: It is my honor to win your trust

1a4b9dc3f2051dd4.voiceContent: As a general rule, the less a person sees of me, the happier their life is

1c719bb7956b0b9a.voiceContent: The Fortress of Meropide works with Spina di Rosula on some matters regarding supplies and logistics, but we don't have any other dealings. This isn't because I don't trust Navia or her abilities, in fact, I hold her in quite high regard. The only reason we continue to stay out of each other's way is because I wanna honor the agreement I made with the late Mr. Callas

266bedc87e2cf013.voiceContent: While I do possess some stereotypical Fontainian looks, when you're an orphan, you can never really be sure where you're from. Who knows, maybe I'll take a dip in the Primordial Sea one of these days just to check..

2dc60fe9384b81a1.voiceContent: Hmm... This is a different kind of cold than what I'm used to

2fc9511a7207c134.voiceContent: If a man will not work, he shall not eat. This phrase has been on the walls of the Fortress of Meropide for as long as anyone can remember. I don't know who first came up with it, but it's been pretty useful in the underworld

30ca34ba03dbd4ae.voiceContent: I was once summoned by Neuvillette to discuss some matters with him in his office. When I approached the Palais Mermonia, I saw him standing by the road, completely drenched in the rain. I held out an umbrella for him, and while he thanked me politely, his expression was a little... distressed, I guess. I can only assume that I had disturbed him in the middle of something

351ecdbf2a9a9770.voiceContent: They say there's nothing new under the sun, but somehow a picnic in the warm sunshine never gets old

40113ff17de6653a.voiceContent: Sigewinne the head nurse possesses all the virtues associated with the medical profession and genuinely cares for the well-being of everyone around her.She seems to have picked up some bad habits from me, though, like frequently betting with her Melusine friends over who'd be able to put more stickers on my belongings. Hm? No, I'm not actually bothered by it

42c09c2f6dd75510.voiceContent: Uh oh, looks like I'll owe you a favor now

434f7d08ad00bdf5.voiceContent: Most inmates seem to gain a new level of respect for the rules after receiving attention from the Special Security and Surveillance Patrol. As the captain, Chevreuse is an instrumental part of that team

45f0ca2f97440aef.voiceContent: Our tradition says that all children of Fontaine are born amid their parents' wishes and blessings, but I'd like to think that all children are born from such wonderful feelings. Anything that I can say to celebrate your birth would feel a little trivial next to that, right?Unfortunately, I won't be able to reduce your prison sentence if you were to commit a crime â€” the only thing I would be able to pull off would be a special Welfare Meal for your birthday dinner. With all that in mind, why don't you try to respect the law a bit more around your birthday, so we'll be able to celebrate somewhere nice on the surface

477ccdc062e549c2.voiceContent: Please excuse me, I'm... I'm gonna brew a cup of tea

5cc7572b82a9259e.voiceContent: Huh, is it evening already? Could have sworn I'd just had my afternoon tea

5e8233223ca76f3d.voiceContent: Stay cool and face your guilt

6121723131e5e746.voiceContent: Sometimes, you have to go all in

64dffaad5b3cd236.voiceContent: They say it's best to begin a friendship when there's no conflict of interest. Seems like the appropriate time has come

6835b1511b194150.voiceContent: All unclaimed articles should be turned in, so... neither of us saw anything here, right

699a9721108d1c15.voiceContent: You know, they say if you're scared of the thunder, it's really because you've got something else to hide

6a7939b4b89f5982.voiceContent: Did you know, many similar models of handcuffs can all be unlocked using the same master key? Except mine, of course. They're different

6c950390fbb139b7.voiceContent: I form my first impressions of many people based on the contents of their inmate registration papers. Seems like you're no exception to the rule

6e11f2616644b66c.voiceContent: Miss Furina displayed a severe lack of interest in my trial and excused herself early, probably because I pleaded guilty to all charges as soon as they were announced. Disappointing the Hydro Archon is a big deal, so... suppose I've got no choice but to keep gifting her copious amounts of the highest quality tea

6ee16e1ac77da304.voiceContent: Morning. What do the papers have to say about today's weather forecast

7002580a4548aa4c.voiceContent: What a perfect blend of flavors. I could have never made this myself

739497bf50f98fe0.voiceContent: The Coupon Cafeteria is probably crowded right now. I'll have someone deliver the food straight to my office

73f1b892ffac8b69.voiceContent: People have this tendency to see me as an all-knowing figure with mystical powers. In reality, I'm just one man with two eyes and two ears. How can I possibly know everything that's happening in the Fortress of Meropide

76102346300d4a30.voiceContent: I'll admit that when I removed the House of the Hearth's spies in the underworld, that was kind of an intentional provocation to the Fatui. But their only response was to send down a bunch of children... Was it because they truly saw those kids as disposable? Or because they knew I wouldn't have it in me to let them come to serious harm? *sigh

8126988648a8ab4f.voiceContent: I'll do my best, but I can't guarantee you victory

8bb8f7de68d21a99.voiceContent: Honestly, my personal abilities are pretty limited. I got no talent in medicine, inventions, or ship-making. But what I do know how to do is find those people with those talents, and get 'em to come work for me

979965d268d351d8.voiceContent: The Fortress of Meropide doesn't need her services. Yet some things are best preserved the way they are, warts and all, so people don't make the same mistakes twice... I say warts, but yeah. I mean the smell

a33e37fd7a44b19a.voiceContent: I like signs of strength and hope. They give me reassurance that tomorrow will be better than today. This isn't to be pessimistic, but it's impossible for the present to be without its doubts and troubles â€” that's just the truth. But come hell or high water, if nothing else then at least we'll be able to figure it out together, right

a4da65937e201326.voiceContent: Lovely. I'll be sure to treat you to something next time

a628f6cf7cee8513.voiceContent: Clorinde is the best Champion Duelist you can find. Her combat prowess is already the stuff of legend. I've never fought her myself, but that's because there's never been a need for it

ad24f14712e89696.voiceContent: Good night. I'll be staying up for a little while yet â€” want to run some numbers while everything's nice and quiet

bbc93d41e4968b2e.voiceContent: Oh, this wasn't locked? How convenient

c0326ea3494496e3.voiceContent: I once considered keeping some pets in my office, but soon gave up on the idea. It's just not right to keep small animals where they won't be able to see the sun

c3c12bab3cdf864b.voiceContent: Hmm? Oh the scar on my body? It's from a gash I got while battling a gigantic undersea monster that tried to take over the Fortress of Meropide. ...Hah, just kidding

c47df6272a777291.voiceContent: Ha, why do you look even more pleased about this than me

c5964320283dcb48.voiceContent: Boxing? To me, that's more of a necessity than a hobby. You got some suggestions for actual hobbies

ca295d657a579b9c.voiceContent: No backup, huh? Fine by me

df0f6fb1f6a8b360.voiceContent: Instead of going big, guess I'm going home..

f304192b1dee246c.voiceContent: This could get a little chilly
